Step 1: Prepare for Deployment
cmd
# Remove Cypress to avoid deployment conflicts
npm uninstall cypress

# Update package-lock.json
npm install

copy package-heroku.json package.json

# Commit the changes
git add package.json package-lock.json
git add .
git commit -m "Deploy: Remove Cypress for production"
Step 2: Deploy to Heroku
cmd
# Push to Heroku
git push heroku main

# Monitor deployment in real-time
heroku logs --tail -a petwell
Step 3: Verify Deployment
cmd
# Check if deployment succeeded
heroku releases -a petwell -n 3

# Open your live app
heroku open -a petwell

# Check app status
heroku ps -a petwell
Step 4: Restore Cypress (for local development)
cmd
# Reinstall Cypress for local testing
npm install cypress --save-dev